The fort - Search NHLs by State," on 12/23/98. consists of 14 stone buildings and two log structures that served as an important post of European-American settlement in the old Northwest.
It was also used as a troop training center in the Civil War and in both World Wars.
Today, the fort is maintained much as it was in the 1800s.
