P A G E 70 ENERGY PRODUCTION 11 Exhibit 9-4 shows the distribution of power in the UMR five-state region based on revenue generated by residential, commercial, industrial, and other users such as public authorities for street lighting and railroad operators.12 Residential users account for the largest share of revenue (41 percent).
Commercial sector consumers represent 29 percent of revenues, using electricity for the lighting, heating, and cooling of commercial buildings (e.g., offices).
Industrial users (26 percent of revenue) include food processors, chemical manufacturers, and transportation equipment producers, among the largest manufacturers in the UMR.
